    &lt;Title&gt;THE ONLY GOOD THING WAS THE FOOD!&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;ABSOLUTELY CHAOTIC!. I missed one visitor because he’d been told I had been discharged! Another visitor  a couple of days later was informed that there was nobody of my name in the hospital! Thankfully he knew I was there and searched the hospital for the right ward, finally finding me. The only praise I can give is for the food, which has vastly improved so please send my compliments to the chefs. Good varied menu which you order the day before.  Always a soup or juice starter, and every soup was delicious.  Shame that’s the only good thing I can think of to say right now.  My stay here was a NIGHTMARE.  I am aware that I have to be careful what I say otherwise my review will not be published…  but I’ll say one thing... I hadn’t bought a pack of cigarettes for a year. The stress I experienced in there had me going outside and smoking TWO CIGARETTES AT A TIME! Thank you stepping hill for that. I feel so much healthier now!&lt;/CommentText&gt;
